devdoc.details: The LeanIMT is an optimized version of the BinaryIMT. This implementation eliminates the use of zeroes, and make the tree depth dynamic. When a node doesn't have the right child, instead of using a zero hash as in the BinaryIMT, the node's value becomes that of its left child. Furthermore, rather than utilizing a static tree depth, it is updated based on the number of leaves in the tree. This approach results in the calculation of significantly fewer hashes, making the tree more efficient.
devdoc.title: Lean Incremental binary Merkle tree.

devdoc.details: This contract allows you to create groups, add, remove and update members. You can use getters to obtain informations about groups (root, depth, number of leaves).

GroupAdminPending(uint256,address,addres.details: Event emitted when a group admin is being updated.

GroupAdminUpdated(uint256,address,addres.details: Event emitted when a new admin is assigned to a group.

GroupCreated(uint256).details: Event emitted when a new group is created.

MemberAdded(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint.details: Event emitted when a new identity commitment is added.

params.merkleTreeRoot: : New root hash of the tree.

MemberRemoved(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.details: Event emitted when a new identity commitment is removed.

params.identityCommitment: : Existing identity commitment to be removed.
params.merkleTreeRoot: : New root hash of the tree.

MemberUpdated(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.details: Event emitted when an identity commitment is updated.

params.identityCommitment: : Existing identity commitment to be updated.
params.merkleTreeRoot: : New root hash of the tree.

MembersAdded(uint256,uint256,uint256[],u.details: Event emitted when many identity commitments are added at the same time.

params.merkleTreeRoot: : New root hash of the tree.
params.startIndex: : Index of the first element of the new identity commitments in the merkle tree.

admins.details: Gets a group id and returns its admin. The admin can be an Ethereum account or a smart contract.

merkleTrees.details: Gets a group id and returns its tree data. The tree is an Incremental Merkle Tree which is called Lean Incremental Merkle Tree.

pendingAdmins.details: Gets a group id and returns any pending admin. The pending admin can be an Ethereum account or a smart contract.

@title Lean Incremental binary Merkle tree.
 @dev The LeanIMT is an optimized version of the BinaryIMT.
 This implementation eliminates the use of zeroes, and make the tree depth dynamic.
 When a node doesn't have the right child, instead of using a zero hash as in the BinaryIMT,
 the node's value becomes that of its left child. Furthermore, rather than utilizing a static tree depth,
 it is updated based on the number of leaves in the tree. This approach
 results in the calculation of significantly fewer hashes, making the tree more efficient.
